description: This library contains the classes with core functionality that drives the the EsentWorkbench desktop application and the esentcmd command line utility. The library was never intended to be used outside of the EsentWorkbench project environment, but it was published anyway in case it might be of interest or use to other developers. The class DatabaseUtility encapsulates most of the important library functionality.
releaseNotes: Corrected byte[] export format to be base64 encoded (Issue #39). ExportBufferFormat enum is deprecated, causing some utility method signatures to change.
summary: A library of classes that implement the core functionality of the Esent Workbench desktop application. This library contains general purpose utility classes that manipulate ESENT (Extensible Storage Engine) databases from managed code. The ManagedEsent package is used to ineroperate with the native esent.dll functions.
